<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FC3BFE6C8356FE67" box="[914,1032,470,490]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFAEFF84FC3BFE6C835AFE67" box="[914,1028,470,490]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Melica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigida">Melica rigida</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FBA2FE6C8341FE67" bold="true" box="[1035,1055,470,490]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">A.</emphasis>
Plants. 
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FBCDFE6C8329FE67" bold="true" box="[1124,1143,470,490]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">B.</emphasis>
Spikelet detail.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF7C93ABFFAEFF84FF01FC3A8536FC3C" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" startId="16.[168,230,896,916]" targetBox="[168,775,160,871]" targetPageId="16">
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFAEFF84FF01FC3A8536FC3C" blockId="16.[168,775,896,945]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FF01FC3A8653FC19" bold="true" box="[168,269,896,916]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">Figure 15.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FEBFFC3A855CFC19" box="[278,514,896,916]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFAEFF84FEBFFC3A86A3FC19" box="[278,509,896,916]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Danthonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montevidensis">Danthonia montevidensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FDA3FC3A8540FC19" bold="true" box="[522,542,896,916]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">A.</emphasis>
Plant with two inflorescences (arrows). 
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FE94FC27860EFC3C" bold="true" box="[317,336,925,945]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">B.</emphasis>
Flower and awn detail (arrow).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF7C93ABFFAEFF84FC84FC7C84EDFC7A" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" startId="16.[813,875,966,986]" targetBox="[813,1420,538,942]" targetPageId="16">
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFAEFF84FC84FC7C84EDFC7A" blockId="16.[813,1420,966,1015]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FC84FC7C84CFFC57" bold="true" box="[813,913,966,986]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">Figure 17.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FC33FC7C8362FC57" box="[922,1084,966,986]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFAEFF84FC33FC7C8366FC57" box="[922,1080,966,986]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Melica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parodiana">Melica parodiana</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FBEAFC7C8309FC57" bold="true" box="[1091,1111,966,986]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">A.</emphasis>
Plant. 
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FB32FC7C83F0FC57" bold="true" box="[1179,1198,966,986]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">B.</emphasis>
Inflorescence detail. 
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FAD0FC7C82D2FC57" bold="true" box="[1401,1420,966,986]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">C.</emphasis>
Spikelet detail.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFAEFF84FF01FC5B8631FB4C" blockId="16.[168,775,993,1451]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">
cence: a loose pubescence panicle, to 
<quantity id="4CFB6EC6FFAEFF84FDE2FC5B85D1FC75" box="[587,655,993,1017]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" unit="cm" value="15.0">15 cm</quantity>
long, with multiflorous lanceolate spikelets. Glumes 
<quantity id="4CFB6EC6FFAEFF84FD22FBB88458FB97" box="[651,774,1026,1050]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" unit="mm" value="23.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="16.0">16–30 mm</quantity>
long, outgrowing flower sets. Spikelets with 5–10 flow- ers; lemma 
<quantity id="4CFB6EC6FFAEFF84FE80FBFF86C9FBD1" box="[297,407,1093,1117]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–4 mm</quantity>
long, ovate-lanceolate, with bifid apex. Central twisted awn brown or colorless, 
<quantity id="4CFB6EC6FFAEFF84FD35FBDC8459FBF3" box="[668,775,1126,1150]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" unit="cm" value="19.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="15.0">15–23 cm</quantity>
long, inserted at bifurcation point of lemma. Fruit: an obovate caryopsis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31990A8FFAEFF84FF67FB708645FA27" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBCC323FFAEFF84FF67FB708645FA27" blockId="16.[168,775,993,1451]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FF67FB70860EFB6F" bold="true" box="[206,336,1226,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">Comments.</emphasis>
This is a frequent species in the study area. It grows in shallow to moderately deep soils on slopes, in grasslands, and around the pond. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C03B8A0FFAEFF84FF6FFA958504FACA" authority="Hack. &amp; Arechav." authorityName="Hack. &amp; Arechav." box="[198,602,1327,1351]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Danthonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cirrata">
<emphasis id="B9771F31FFAEFF84FF6FFA9586D4FACB" box="[198,394,1327,1351]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1019">Danthonia cirrata</emphasis>
Hack. &amp; Arechav.
</taxonomicName>
, which also has been found in the Paititi Reserve, but the lemma of the latter species has the lateral lobes longer than the undivided part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
